Sirrion can be fun. He's a flamegod that many don't like, but that's ok. He doesn't care about that. He just likes flames. I do too.
- Kender Child explaining Krynn mythology</p>
Sirrion is the husband of Shinare. Iyachtu Xvim posed as him during his attempt at stealing the divine power from Tymora and Beshaba. Sirrion dwells in Limbo in a Realm called the Flame Void.</p>
Sources: Dragonlance Adventures, Dragonlance Campaign Setting (Third Edition), On Hallowed Ground